      "content": "f(x) = 3x^2 + 2x - 5",
      "narration": "Find the derivative of f of x equals 3x squared plus 2x minus 5.",
      "mode": "replace",
      "label": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "box",
      "content": "\\text{Power Rule: } \\frac{d}{dx}[x^n] = nx^{n-1}",
      "narration": "We'll use the power rule \u2014 bring the exponent down and subtract one.",
      "mode": "replace",
      "label": "Key Rule"
    },
    {
      "type": "transform",
      "content": "f'(x) = \\frac{d}{dx}[3x^2] + \\frac{d}{dx}[2x] - \\frac{d}{dx}[5]",
      "narration": "Take the derivative term by term.",
      "mode": "replace",
      "label": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "transform",
      "content": "f'(x) = 3 \\cdot 2x^{1} + 2 \\cdot 1x^{0} - 0",
      "narration": "Apply the power rule to each term.",
      "mode": "replace",
      "label": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "graph",
